nodes.title: STEP I
widgets_values:
1) UPLOAD THE IMAGE IF YOU WANT TO WORK ON IT, 
   OTHERWISE SKIP IT. 
   YOU CAN ADD MASK ON IMAGE AND FROM PROMPTS.
   YOU CAN USE TWO MASK SOURCE AT THE SAME 
   TIME THEY ARE COMBINED.
   IF MASK FROM PROMT MARK TOO MANY THINGS 
   INCRISE A MASK STRENGTH.
   YOU CAN ALSO INVERT MASK TO CHANGE 
   EVERYTHING EXCEPT MARKED ITEMS.
   REMEMBER TO RESET MASK ON IMAGE WHEN YOU 
   LOAD IMAGE (ON START TOO).

2) GIVE PROMPTS: 
 -POSITIVE (WHAT YOU WANT TO GET),
 -NEGATIVE (WHAT YOU DON'T WANT IN THE IMAGE)

3) CHOOSE A BASIC MODEL

5) SET THE RESOLUTION (EMPTY LATENT):
 -PREFERABLY FOR SDXL MODEL:
  1024 X 1024 - 1:1
  1152 X 896 - 9:7
  1216 X 832 - 3:2
  1344 X 768 - 16:9
  1536 X 640 - 12:5

nodes.title: STEP II
widgets_values:
1) CHOOSE WHAT YOU WANT TO DO:
 1 - TEXT TO IMAGE
 2 - IMAGE TO IMAGE
 3 - IMAGE TO IMAGE - INPAINTING (ADD MASK),
     AND SET "GROW BY MASK" VALUE
 4 - IMAGE TO IMAGE - KEEP SHAPE
 5 - CHANGE LOADED IMAGE STYLE
 6 - UPSCALE LOADED IMAGE
 7 - DRAW AND GENERATE (USE LCM SAMPLER AND LCM 
     LORA) - IN GROUP "DRAW AND GENERATE" 
     TOOGLE OPTION (EXTRA OPTIONS -> AUTO QUEUE) 
     TO GENERATE ALMOST IN REAL TIME.
 8 - SEAMLESS TEXTURE (BASED ON LOADED IMAGE 
     RESOLUTION) - DENOISE INCLUDED
 9 - SCRATCH TO IMAGE (CANNY)

2) SET GROW MASK IF USING MASK

3) SET DENOISE IF YOU WORKING ON LOADED IMAGE:
   (UPSCALE TOO) (0.01 - 1.00)
 0 - !!! NO DEVIDE BY 0 !!! SET 0.01 MIN 
 0.3 - ADD DETAILS ONLY
 0.7 - A LOT OF CHANGES
 1 - SAME RESOLUTION DIFFERENT IMAGE

4) SET UPSCALE VALUE - MULTIPLIES THE RESOLUTION 
   BY THE SPECIFIED VALUE

5) CHOOSE STYLE - IF YOU WANT SWAP STYLE

6) SET STRENGHT OF CONTROLNETS (0.01-1.00)

7) SET SCRATCH TYPE: 
 1 - CANNY (BLACK BACGROUND AND WHITE LINES)
 2 - DRAW (WHITE BACKGROUND AND BLACK LINES)

8) LOAD THE LORA (OPTIONAL) - REMEMBER TO LOAD 
   THE LORE CORRESPONDING TO THE MODEL, 
   OTHERWISE IT WILL NOT WORK PROPERLY.
   TOOGLE SWITCH TO ON/OFF AND SET LORA STRENGTH 
   (0.01-1.00)

nodes.title: MANUAL
widgets_values:
VERSION 5
EXAMPLES HOW TO USE THIS WORKFLOW:
(STEP III NOT EXPLAINED)

1) TEXT TO IMAGE:
   
   STEP I:
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   - SET RESOLUTION (WANT 1344X768 BUT IN PORTREIT - 1344 AS HEIGHT , 768 AS WIDTH)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 1
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK

2) IMAGE TO IMAGE:

   STEP I:
   - LOAD IMAGE
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 2
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 0.01 - 1.00
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK
   
3) IMAGE TO IMAGE - INPAINTING:

   STEP I:
   - LOAD IMAGE
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - ADD MASK (ON IMAGE OR BY PROMPTS OR BY BOTH OPTIONS)
   - SET STRENGHT MASK (IF YOU USING MASK BY PROMPT)
   - SET MASK INVERSION (FOR EX. IF YOU MARK ITEM/OBJECT AND WAND CHCGE BACKGROUND THEN SET VALUE 2)
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 3
   - SET GROW MASK VALUE: INTEGER VALUES
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 0.01 - 1.00
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK

4) IMAGE TO IMAGE - KEEP SHAPE:

   STEP I:
   - LOAD IMAGE
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 4
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 0.01 - 1.00
   - SET CONTROLNET STRENGHT
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK

5) CHANGE LOADED IMAGE STYLE:

   STEP I:
   - LOAD IMAGE
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 5
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 0.01 - 1.00
   - CHOOSE STYLE
   - SET CONTROLNET STRENGHT
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK (STYLE LORA RECOMENDED, I USING "Nordic Modern Interior Style.safetensor")

6) UPSCALE LOADED IMAGE:

   STEP I:
   - LOAD IMAGE
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 6
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 0.01 - 1.00
   - SET UPSCALE VALUE (FOR EX. IMAGE 1024X1024 VALUE 0.5 => 512X512 , IMAGE 1024X1024 VALUE 2 => 2048X2048)
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK

7) DRAW AND GENERATE: 

   STEP I:
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 7
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 0.01 - 1.00 (RECOMENDED ~ 0.65)
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK
   DRAW AND GENERATE:
   - PRESS EDIT TO OPEN NEW WINDOW AND DRAW
   - (OPTIONAL) TOOGLE AUTO GENERATION (IN MENU: EXTRA OPTIONS => AUTO QUEUE)

8) SEAMLESS TEXTURE (RESOLUTION BASED ON LOADED IMAGE):

   STEP I:
   - LOAD IMAGE
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 8
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 0.01 - 1.00
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK

9) SCRATCH TO IMAGE:

   STEP I:
   - LOAD IMAGE
   - FILL POSITIVE AND NEGATIVE NODES
   - LOAD MODEL (CHECKPOINT)
   STEP II:
   - SET OPTION VALUE: 9
   - SET DENOISE VALUE: 1.00
   - SET SCRATH TYPE ( 1 - BLACK BACGROUND WITH WHITE LINES / 2 - WHITE BACKGROUND WITH BLACK LINES)
   - (OPTIONAL) ADD LORA IN LORA_STACK



IMPORTANT:
- DO NOT SET 0 AS DENOISE VALUE (DO NOT DEVIDE BY 0)
- IF YOU LOAD IMAGE (EVEN ON START) U MUST RESET MASK FOR THIS IMAGE BY (OR U CAN GET WRONG MASK): 
  - RIGHT CLICK ON IMAGE 
  - CHOOSE OPTION "OPEN IN MASK EDITOR"
  - PRESS "CLEAR"
  - PRESS "SAVE TO NODE"
- FOR OPTION "DRAW AND GENERATE" RECOMENDED IS USE (WHEN U WANT LIVE GENERATE) 
  SAMPLER_NAME: "LCM", LCM LORA, 5-10 STEPS.
- THERE IS NO NODE NAMED "SAVE IMAGE" BC I USE PYSSSS EXTENSION I RECOMEND USE IT
- REMEMBER TO USE OPTION ON GROUPS "Set Groups Nodes to Never" IF U DONT WANT USE IT (UPSCALE GROUP IN FIRST GO, BC IT 
  WILL UPSCALE BUT IF U USE OTHER OPTION THAN UPSCALE U WILL NOT RECIVE UPSCALED IMMAGE AND IS SLOW) - I STILL WAITING 
  ON WORKING VERSION WITH TRIGGERS :P
